When traveling across the country to bring accolades and respect to your city via your poetry; sometimes you fear if your city is receptive and or appreciative of the work you're doing in their name. In 2022 I have been honored to be Baltimore's Grand Slam champion, @dmvrenaissanceawards recipient of Male Poet Of The Year and Slam Champion Of The Year, and last but not least Baltimore Crown Awards Poet Of The Year. I do not take these honors lightly. Every award is a battery in my back to keep representing my area in a dominant manner. Thank you all for choosing me as your champion 🏆. Thank you God for the opportunity to prove myself time and time again.

#battlepoet #blackchakra #champion #streetsneedabody #streetsneedahero

Thus, this is a conversation I felt had to be put on stage. Aka ‘Isis’ — “She released her debut album ‘Rebel Soul’ under the name Isis while affiliated with X-Clan in 1990. She was a member of the hip-hop collective known as the Blackwatch Movement (which included X Clan). On Billboard.com, Andy Kellman Rovi believed that since Professor X took the mic after almost every verse, it was an X-Clan album in every sense but the name.[1] According to an AllMusic Review by Alex Henderson, Isis “showed a lot of potential on Rebel Soul, which proves that her rapping skills were strong and that her technique was excellent.”

Lin Que left X-Clan and later began to work with MC Lyte. Now rhyming under her birth name Lin Que, and released a couple of singles for Ruffhouse/Columbia Records and EastWest Records America.” 👀👀👀

This Hall of Fame Inductee - man-  we @thebaltimorescene remember him being a youth artist then becoming an adult artist then repeatedly winning basically every poetry slam and competition known to man Nationally  and making Baltimore Internationally known for genius wordplay. 

Not only did Black Chakra leave a legacy with his own art but he also fathered a squad of poets that took on his name and became international champions in their own right as his mentees. 

But wait — there’s more.. he also teaches and coaches countless students in poetry and hip hop in various schools and art programs in addition to being lead coach to Baltimore’s youth poetry slam team carrying on the torch of impeccable writing, fiery passionate performance, and the art of channeling social activism and healing onto the page and the stage. Salute to someone who should always be recognized as someone who has creatively fathered a new generation of creatives as well as innovating a new brand of poetry giving him the title of a Battle Poet-

Come on Saturday IN PURPLE  so we can thank him for putting Baltimore on an international map and for ushering generations of next level poets and hip hop artists 

His bio 

Black Chakra is a spoken word and hip-hop artist whose talents have been showcased on stages across America. In his time competing in poetry slam competitions, he has been a national poetry slam champion, Texas Grand Slam champion, 4 Time Southern Fried slam champion, Rustbelt Slam Champion, Black Arts Matter Slam Champion, Exit 36 Slam Champion, and a plethora of others too long to list. Black Chakra embodies the city of Baltimore through aggressive performance and incredible writing. Next to being a talented writer, what he takes most pride in is being a youth poetry teacher for Dewmore  Baltimore. He helps Baltimore youths cultivate their talent and showcase it on National stages.#baltimorecrownawards #thebaltimorescene #baltimore #blackchakra #baltimorepoetry #dewmorepoetry #poetry #spokenword #baltimoreevents #visitbaltimore #thingstodoinbaltimore
